Description: Naruto and his allies face off against a horde of ninja soldiers, some of whom are back from the dead and former friends.
Title: NARUTO, VOL. 56
Author: Masashi Kishimoto

Description: Sailor Moon fights for justice in the name of the Moon and the mysterious Moon Princess. Along the way, she recruits other girls to be Sailor Scouts and join her fight against evil.
Title: SAILOR MOON, VOL. 5
Author: Naoko Takeuchi

Description: Monkey D. Luffy and his motley crew of would-be pirates search for a legendary treasure called “One Piece.” In this volume, the crew set sail for Fish-man Island at the bottom of the sea.
Title: ONE PIECE, VOL. 62
Author: Eiichiro Oda

Description: Negi, the boy wizard, learns he will be teaching English at an all-girls high school in Japan, but he must keep his powers a secret.
Title: NEGIMA! MAGISTER NEGI MAGI, VOL. 34
Author: Ken Akamatsu

Description: The Pokemon saga continues with the introduction of two new trainers: Black and White.
Title: POKEMON BLACK AND WHITE, VOL. 7
Author: Hidenori Kusaka

Description: Welcome to Academy City, which teems with psychics. One of them is Mikoto Misaka, who investigates the dark side of things.
Title: A CERTAIN SCIENTIFIC RAILGUN, VOL. 4
Author: Kazuma Kamachi

Description: Ageha Yoshina is searching for a friend who has gone missing and he finds himself in a deadly game with the Psyren Secret Society.
Title: PSYREN, VOL. 4
Author: Toshiaki Iwashiro

Description: Whether rain, shine, sun or snow, the Letter Bee is "entrusted to deliver the hearts of people separated from the ones they love."
Title: TEGAMI BACHI, VOL. 9
Author: Hiroyuki Asada

Description: From the publisher: "Shurei Hong, destitute but of noble birth, has always dreamed of working as a civil servant in the imperial court of Saiunkoku, but women are barred from holding office."
Title: THE STORY OF SAIUNKOKU, VOL. 7
Author: Sai Yukino

Description: Mizuki is the the lead guitarist in an all-girl rock band. Akira is from an all-boy school and wants to join. In this volume, Akira's middle school tutor has returned and threatens to reveal a secret from his past.
Title: AI ORE: LOVE ME, VOL. 5
Author: Mayu Shinjo
